Description: Lower body and ring foot of South Ionian pottery cup; interior glazed save for tondo, on which there is a black dot and ring; exterior: glazed above band at turn to foot; black band on interior surface of foot; at centre of underside of bowl black dot and ring; inscription on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 375)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.831)
